AB  - The welfare consequences of price instability for internationally traded goods critically depend on whether tariffs or marketing boards are present. For example, unlike in the free trade case, when the source of price instability is external, the importing country prefers price stability where trade is restricted by tariffs. The opposite is true, however, when trade is restricted by marketing boards.
